Description: Library that supports visual interpretation of
        hierarchical composite endpoints (HCEs). HCEs are complex
        constructs used as primary endpoints in clinical trials,
        combining outcomes of different types into ordinal endpoints,
        in which each patient contributes the most clinically important
        event (one and only one) to the analysis. See Karpefors M et
        al. (2022) <doi:10.1177/17407745221134949>.
